description: Need a healthier school holiday snack for hungry tummies? Try this budget recipe for chicken rissole bites. They're packed with vegies, but don't tell the kids.
keywords: Rissoles,Zucchini,High protein,Low salt,Tree nut free,Mince,Healthier Easier,Low sugar,Chicken,Peanut free
name: Chicken Rissole Bites Recipe | Woolworths
recipeIngredient: 250g Macro Organic bolognese chunky pasta sauce

recipeInstructions.text: Preheat oven to 200°C/180°C fan-forced. Line a baking tray with baking paper.

Combine chicken, egg, cheese, breadcrumbs, carrot and zucchini in a large bowl Season with pepper. Shape 2 tablespoonfuls of mixture into round patties to make a total of 20. Place, evenly spaced, on tray. Spray with oil and bake for 30 minutes or until golden and cooked through.
Meanwhile, place sauce in a small saucepan over medium heat. Cook, stirring occasionally for 3 minutes or until heated through. Serve rissoles with sauce.
